<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>'s largest peace movement has come under a new barrage of criticism from hawks and Prime Minister <PERSON> Yitzhak </PERSON> <PERSON> Shamir </PERSON> is heading the attacks by questioning group members' loyalty to their country. <PERSON> Shamir </PERSON>'s remarks Sunday that Peace Now activists are in cahoots with `` the most dangerous and extremist of our enemies'' triggered a barrage of accusations and counterattacks. Peace Now members, like all other <LOCATION> Israeli </LOCATION> citizens, serve in the armed forces and do annual reserve duty. `` They are sabotaging <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>'s political war, the war for <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>'s security ... They are helping the most dangerous and most extremist of our enemies,'' <PERSON> Shamir </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Tzahi </PERSON> <PERSON> Hanegbi </PERSON>, a member of <PERSON> Shamir </PERSON>'s hard-line <ORGANIZATION> Likud </ORGANIZATION> bloc, agreed. `` At the height of the uprising when there are blood riots and Jews are being murdered, they -LRB- Peace Now members -RRB- go crawling toward the leaders of the uprising and break a rule that every self-respecting Jew abides, which is to wait for the government's decisions,'' <PERSON> Hanegbi </PERSON> said He was referring to the actions Saturday of thousands of Peace Now members, who tried to drive into the occupied territories to talk peace with Palestinians. The army, which bars political activity in the occupied areas, sealed the <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION> and turned back activists headed to <PERSON> Arab </PERSON> villages. Underlying the attacks on Peace Now, however, is the group's controversial decision several months ago to change its stand toward the <ORGANIZATION> Palestine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION> _ which right-wing circles still consider a terrorist organization dedicated to the destruction of <