<BYLINE>AP Television Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> won the ratings for the 37th week in a row, but which network is second for the season depends on whose compilation of the Nielsen ratings you use. All three networks agree that <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> CBS </ORGANIZATION> tied for second place for the week ended March 5. But, with the season due to end April 23, the networks disagree on second place for the season-to-date. <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>'s wins go back to last season. <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> was the unquestioned winner for the week ended March 5 with a 16.1 rating and a share of 26 in the <ORGANIZATION> A.C. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nielsen </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> listing. <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> CBS </ORGANIZATION> tied for the past week with 12.6 and a 20 share. Each ratings point represents 904,000 homes with television. The share is a percentage of the sets in use. The past week offered no surprises in the listings, with <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` The Cosby Show'' still in first place <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` The Wonder Years'' was in eighth place after its move to Tuesday night between `` Who's the Boss? in seventh place, and `` Roseanne,'' in third place. <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>, which lists the beginning of the season as Sept. 19, put <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> in second place after 24 weeks. Its season-to-date ratings are <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> 12.9 with a 21 percent share and <ORGANIZATION> CBS </ORGANIZATION> 12.6 with a 20 share. <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> leads season-to-date with a rating of 16.0 and a 26 share. <ORGANIZATION> CBS </ORGANIZATION>, counting the season from Oct. 24, lists itself in second place with a 12.9 rating and a 21 share. It gives <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> 12.8 and a 21 share. <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION>'s <PERSON> Nielsen </PERSON> listings put <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> CBS </ORGANIZATION> in a tie with 12.8 each. It also counts the season from Oct. 24. The difference in the season beginning is due to the writers strike last summer, which caused a delay in the premieres of many series. <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> set the season opening at the traditional start time because it had the Summer Olympics from <LOCATION> Seoul </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Korea </LOCATION>. Differences may also result from interpretations by the networks of the raw data from <LOCATION> Nielsen </LOCATION>. It appeared that <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> would finish in second place for the second year, but <ORGANIZATION> CBS </ORGANIZATION> became a contender with the miniseries `` Lonesome Dove.'' The Top 10 this past week was dominated by two nights, <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>'s Thursday comedies and <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION>'s Tuesday comedies All four <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> Thursday shows were at the top, as were three <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> shows. <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION>'s new comedy `` Coach,'' which had a special preview following `` Roseanne'' on Tuesday, placed 11th. But for its premiere in its regular Wednesday time slot the show dropped to 46th place. Here are the Top 10: <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` The Cosby Show,'' <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` A Different World,'' <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` Roseanne,'' <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` Cheers,'' <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` Golden Girls,'' <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` Who's the Boss?,'' CBS' `` 60 Minutes,'' <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` The Wonder Years,'' <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` Empty Nest'' and <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` Dear <PERSON> John </PERSON>. The CBS special movie `` Day One'' was 29th in the ratings. The premiere of the CBS series `` Hard Time on Planet Earth'' was 