<HEAD>Kohl Calls On Soviets To Withdraw Chemical Weapons From Europe</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Baker, Bjt</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By GIRARD C. STEICHEN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>BONN, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The government on Tuesday urged the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION> to remove its chemical weapons from <LOCATION> Eastern </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION> and destroy them. The appeal followed a <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> proposal to speed the removal of chemical weapons from <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION>. Chancellor <PERSON> Helmut </PERSON> <PERSON> Kohl </PERSON>, in a news release, said the Soviets and <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> have a unique opportunity to make significant progress in ending the threat of chemical warfare. `` The <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> has taken a step that the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION> and its allies should now follow without delay,'' <PERSON> Kohl </PERSON> said. Referring to the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> proposal, he said, `` I call on the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION> in turn to pull out its chemical weapons stationed in <LOCATION> Eastern </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION> and to destroy them.'' West German opposition leaders have said the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> proposal was vague and disappointing. On Monday, Secretary of State <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> A. </PERSON> <PERSON> Baker </PERSON> said President <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> wanted to explore ways to accelerate the removal of <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> chemical weapons from <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION>. `` The <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> is prepared to lead in dealing with this problem,'' <PERSON> Baker </PERSON> said, but the early removal of the chemical weapons will require `` safe storage and the development of practical plans to destroy them.'' He also said the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION> has enormous stocks of such weapons threatening <LOCATION> Western </LOCATION> <LO