<HEAD>Slovenian Party Leadership Calls For End To Single-Party Rule</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BELGRADE, Yugoslavia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The <ORGANIZATION> Communist </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> leadership in the republic of <LOCATION> Slovenia </LOCATION> has issued an unprecedented call for ending single-party rule in <LOCATION> Yugoslavia </LOCATION>, newspapers said Tuesday. The party leadership in <LOCATION> Slovenia </LOCATION>, the most westward-looking of <LOCATION> Yugoslavia </LOCATION>'s six republics, has long advocated the necessity of radical reforms in overcoming the country's worst social and economic crisis. This was the first time, however, that the party's ruling presidium has come out openly in favor of ending one-party rule. `` The end must come to socialist -LRB- Communist -RRB- and all other fundamentalisms,'' said a document formally adopted Monday by <LOCATION> Slovenia </LOCATION>'s party presidium. The document, published Tuesday by the <ORGANIZATION> Vecernje </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Novosti </ORGANIZATION> daily, was intended to serve as a guideline for upcoming political and economic reforms in <LOCATION> Yugoslavia </LOCATION>. It alluded to traditional beliefs based on a literal interpretation of Marxism-Leninism and regarded as fundamental to Communist faith. `` Instead of ... single-party rule ... political pluralism should be affirmed,'' the document said. The party will support `` freedom, democracy, political pluralism, economic efficiency'' and the creation of an `` affluent society within <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION>,'' Vjesnik, another daily, quoted the statement as saying. <LOCATION> Yugoslavia </LOCATION> has been a single-party state since 1946, when the <ORGANIZATION> Communist </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> abolished all forms of opposition. Recently, however, a number of alternative groups, including a full-fledged <ORGANIZATION> Social </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION>, have been set up in <LOCATION> Slovenia </LOCATION> and in the neighbori