<HEAD>Fair Trade Commission Raids Beef Importers in Pricing Case</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The Fair Trade Commission raided trading companies and their beef trade association Tuesday to investigate an alleged cartel to push up prices of imported beef, officials said. Inspectors went to 29 trading companies, including <ORGANIZATION> Mitsubishi </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Mitsui </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, and <PERSON> C. </PERSON> <PERSON> Itoh </PERSON> and Co.. <ORGANIZATION> Ltd. </ORGANIZATION>, and to the <ORGANIZATION> Japan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Beef </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Importers </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ' </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION>, said <ORGANIZATION> FTC </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Mitsuru </PERSON> <PERSON> Suzuki </PERSON> All 29 companies belong to the 36-member semi-governmental <ORGANIZATION> Livestock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Industry </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Promotion </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> `` We have kept our eyes on them for almost four years,'' he said, adding that the <ORGANIZATION> FTC </ORGANIZATION> suspected the traders since 1984 had been fixing the share of imported beef each would sell to the <ORGANIZATION> LIPC </ORGANIZATION> before actual bidding took place. `` By fixing each company's share, the cartel prevents free competition in the market and raises beef prices,'' <PERSON> Suzuki </PERSON> said. The illegal practice no longer exists, but investigations under the anti-cartel law can go into past actions, <PERSON> Suzuki </PERSON> said. A group of 36 beef importers arranges imports, pays tariffs and sells their imported beef to the <ORGANIZATION> LIPC </ORGANIZATION>, which controls some 90 percent of beef imports. <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION> imported 214,000 tons of beef in 1987 and 175,000 tons were sold through the LIPC. When the issue of a suspected illegal cartel was raised last August, the <ORGANIZATION> LIPC </ORGANIZATION> conducted its own investigation of member companies at government order, said <PERSON> Shinzo </PERSON> <PERSON> Nakatani </PERSON> of the <ORGANIZATION> LIPC </ORGANIZATION>. `` We could n't find anything that indicated the existence of preliminary arrangements to fix shares,'' he added. An official at the <ORGANIZATION> Ministry </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Agriculture </ORGANIZATION>, Forestry and Fisheries said officials in the ministry's livestock department were surprised to learn of the <ORGANIZATION> FTC </ORGANIZATION> raid. The ministry said in a statement that it would take strict measures based on results of the <ORGANIZATION> FTC </ORGANIZATION>'s investigation.
