production. The employee recall will bring to about 4,500 the number of workers at the <ORGANIZATION> Buick </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> City </ORGANIZATION> assembly plant. In October 1987, <ORGANIZATION> GM </ORGANIZATION> laid off about 2,000 workers because of sagging LeSabre sales, <PERSON> Hamp </PERSON> said.
