ak </ORGANIZATION> order was not mentioned in the appeal papers. <PERSON> Sheldon </PERSON> <PERSON> Engelhard </PERSON>, a lawyer for the union, said it would ask the <ORGANIZATION> 2nd </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Circuit </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Appeals </ORGANIZATION> to hear an appeal of <PERSON> Patterson </PERSON>'s orders Tuesday. He said the machinists union is legally entitled to set up secondary picket lines and the rail workers' contracts state they ca n't cross picket lines. Union spokesman <PERSON> Jim </PERSON> <PERSON> Conley </PERSON> would not say if the union planned to picket the railroads if the temporary restraining orders are lifted. `` That's part of the overall strike strategy and it wo n't be released ahead of time,'' <PERSON> Conley </PERSON> said.
