<HEAD>London Shares Close Higher On Strong Pound</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Share prices closed higher Tuesday on the <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> stock exchange, helped by the pound's strength against the West German mark. But prices finished well below their best levels after drifting lower in the afternoon on the back of a weak start to trading on Wall Street. Also knocking shares from their peaks was psychological resistance as the <ORGANIZATION> Financial </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Times-Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> 100-share index bumped up against the 2,100-point level, traders said. `` There is a reticence to go through a distinct chart level,'' said an equity sales manager at a British brokerage firm. At the close, the 100-share index was up 10.7 points, or 0.5 percent, at 2,083.5, marking the sixth rise in a row. Volume stepped up to 583 million shares from 472.9 million shares on Monday.
